com.teamdev.jxbrowser.chromium

Interface HttpHeaders


  • public interface HttpHeaders
    Represents HTTP request and response headers, mapping string header names to list of header values. Header names are case-insensitive.
    表示HTTP请求和响应标头，将字符串标头名称映射到标头值列表。标头名称不区分大小写。

    • Method Detail

      • setHeader

        void setHeader(java.lang.String headerName,
               java.lang.String headerValue)
        Sets a new header using headerName as key and headerValue as value. If such a header already exists, it will be overridden.
        使用headerName作为键和headerValue作为值来设置新的头。如果这样的标头已经存在，它将被覆盖。
        Parameters:
        headerName - case-insensitive header name. -不区分大小写的标头名称。
        headerValue - header value. -标头值。
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when headerName is null or empty, headerValue is null.

      • removeHeader

        java.lang.String removeHeader(java.lang.String headerName)
        Removes a header with the header name defined by headerName
        删除标题由headerName定义的标题
        Parameters:
        headerName - case-insensitive header name. -不区分大小写的标头名称。
        Returns:
        header value which has been removed or null if header with this headerName does not exists. 标头值已被删除，或者标头值不存在。
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - when headerName is null or empty.

      • removeAll

        void removeAll()
        Removes all headers.

      • getHeaders

        java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getHeaders()

        Returns:
